      "acceptanceCriteria": "Primary QoI (relative hemolysis index RH) must be directly computable from CFD outputs and clinically relevant to CPB hemolysis assessment.",
      "rationale": "RH index computed from volume-averaged shear stress and exposure time using the Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law model. RH directly links to plasma-free hemoglobin elevation, the clinical endpoint of concern. Level 2 relevance confirmed."
